{
  "texts": [
    "Specifically, for a fixed duration of simulation time t total, we measure the sliding time, t slide, defined as the cumulative time when CAPs are in contact with the surface of obstacles (i.e., there exists an obstacle i such that jr Àr i j ≤ R).",
    "Particle hopping time is then defined via t hop = t total -t slide.",
    "During sliding, we count the number of occurrences of reversible motion of the particle as N (i.e., particle's tangential velocity with respect to the obstacle surface normal changes sign).",
    "Both parameters we have measured show strong positive correlations with Ψ, indicating that they dominate the diffusion constant D eff (Fig. 6).",
    "To understand, note that the diffusion of CAPs is primarily driven by their ability to hop to the next row of obstacles, which effectively initiates a new orbit."
  ]
}